<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1196">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/6958.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, representing American
                                interests</hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>141. American settlers in Yaqui Valley, Sonora, complain of inadequate
                            protection against Indians. Urge appropriate authorities to issue orders
                            immediately to General Dieguez to send at least three hundred soldiers
                            to Yaqui Valley.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>